      <h2 class="c1" id="h.sj6axoibk1ay"><span class="c4">Ng-bind</span></h2>
      <p class="c7"><span class="c5">A more explicit way of inserting scoped content into your html. &nbsp;Assume a controller is in scope with an available &lsquo;foo&rsquo; property. &nbsp;These two are the same:</span></p>
      <p class="c7 c10"><span class="c0">&lt;span&gt;{{foo}}&lt;/span&gt;</span></p>
      <p class="c7 c10"><span class="c0">&lt;span ng-bind=&rdquo;foo&rdquo;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</span></p>
      <p class="c7"><span class="c5">Also, keep in mind that an ng-bind expression can be more complicated. &nbsp;These two are also the same:</span></p>
      <p class="c7 c10"><span class="c0">&lt;span&gt;foo is: {{foo}}&lt;/span&gt;</span></p>
      <p class="c7 c10"><span class="c0">&lt;div ng-bind=&quot;&#39;foo is: &#39; + foo&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span></p>
